## Surgical Changes Constraint (Karpathy Rule)

**Only modify the exact lines required by the task. Never edit adjacent code.**

- Read the task. Identify the minimum set of lines that must change.
- Change only those lines. Leave everything else untouched.
- If you find a "while I'm here" improvement nearby, **do not make it**. File a separate note but do not touch it.
- Every line you change beyond the task scope increases regression risk and creates review noise.
- This rule applies even when adjacent code looks wrong or could be improved.

