## Architecture Principles

### Before writing code, state:
1. What is the data flow? (source → transform → sink)
2. What are the failure modes? (network, auth, data, infra)
3. What is the right abstraction boundary?

### When to reach for each pattern

| Pattern | Use when |
|---------|---------|
| Repository pattern | Multiple data sources, want to test without DB |
| Service layer | Business logic spans multiple models |
| Event-driven | Decoupled side effects, audit trail, replay |
| CQRS | Read/write traffic patterns differ significantly |
| Circuit breaker | Calling unreliable external services |

### File organization

Python:
```
app/
  routers/     # Route handlers — thin, delegate to services
  services/    # Business logic — no direct DB access
  models/      # Pydantic input/output + SQLAlchemy ORM
  core/        # Config, deps, middleware, exceptions
  utils/       # Pure functions
```

TypeScript:
```
src/
  components/  # React components (common/ + feature-specific)
  hooks/       # Custom hooks
  lib/         # api.ts, utils.ts
  types/       # Shared type definitions
  pages/       # One file per route
```

